===Etymology===
From {{etyl|grc|en}} {{m|grc|κεραμικός||potter's}}, from {{m|grc|κέραμος||potter's clay}}, perhaps from a pre-Hellenic word.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|GenAm|RP}} {{IPA|/səˈɹæmɪk/|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|æmɪk|lang=en}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|-}}

# made of material produced by the high temperature firing of inorganic, nonmetallic rocks and minerals.
#: ''A ceramic vase stood on the table.''

